BENIN â€“ Mr. Godwin Nogheghase Obaseki, Governor of Edo State, has appointed nine new Permanent Secretaries, including the general manager of Observer group of Newspapers, Mr. Imoihosen Solomon Oziegbe in the state Civil Service: A statement signed by the Secretary to the state government (SSG) Osarodion Ogie Esq. gave the names of the newly appointed Permanent secretaries as Iryn Ekhorose Omorogiuwa, Efosa Aisien, Nyamali Joseph Frumuse and Igbinomwanhia Naps Abieyuwa, Others are Imoihosen Solomon Oziegbe, Peter Aibuedefe Osagie, Sabina A. Chikere, Osawemwenze Edith Kayode-lyasere and Bernard Aigbe. The SSG, in the statement stated that the swearing-in of the appointees will be announced at a later date.